Free
From iA wiki
See also: Open Source | Free Software Foundation | Non-Free | Free Speech
Free means without ownership, restriction or barter. Things may be free but still moderated by things other than cost or availability.
What restrictions exist on being free is a subject of much concern. In particular, the Free Software movement has adopted several concepts to further elaborate on the concept of "free". Two phrases that are frequantly used:
"Free" is different from "Freedom".
"Free as in speech": (aka "Free as in Libre") - a concept that a freedom with any restrictions results in not being free at all. When applied to software, it describes a lack of restriction with the acquisition, use, modification and distribution; that the software can be universally 'made useful'. In discussion
